reviews.review_text: fob nirvana Yessss boys and girls. At last a great recording of a kick-ass show. The band is pissed off and he vibe is snarly, a typical NY state show akin to the Saratoga triple play of the same period. The Jack Straw will blow the hair off your scalp if listened to at high volume and the Shakedown is as funkedelic as it gets. The Weir growls in the Smokestacks are classic (and up front you thought that you had the best spot in the house before the showers began) and the jam out of the song is a real treat. I must say that the stunning fobs posted on the Archive have me checking daily for the updates.

What Rhymes with Orange?? Nothing!  Great setlist and decent performance, although--and it pains me to say this--Jerry voice is hurting and he muddles through several of the songs.  If nothing else the He's Gone>Smokestack>Jam part was pretty hot so I'll give it a 4.
Sounds great Good show, great recording...
Carry me Dome Yes a screaming Jack Straw-and even a couple of cool Take a step backs! Don't forget-Bob is The Other One-and here he shows you why.
